'''Chemical safety''' is the practice of handling chemicals in a safe manner, minimizing the [[Chemical hazard|hazard]] to [[public health|public]] and personal [[health]].
==Principles== Chemical safety is the practice of minimizing risk of exposure to chemicals in any environment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cenblog.org/the-safety-zone/2013/03/defining-chemical-safety-health-hygiene-and-security/|title=Defining chemical safety, health, hygiene, and security|date=2013-03-27|language=en-US|access-date=2016-07-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.who.int/topics/chemical_safety/en/|title=Chemical safety|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=World Health Organization|access-date=}}</ref>
Despite efforts to design in and maintain safety, accidents happen.{{sfn|Hall|p. 3}}
==Occupational safety and health== {{main|Occupational safety and health}} Governments regulate workplace health and safety.
