{{UK-geologist-stub}} {{palaeontologist-stub}}

'''Ionization cones''' are cones of material extending out from [[spiral galaxy|spiral galaxies]].  They are visible because of their emissions which are believed to be from re-emission of [[photons]] produced by nuclear activity within the galaxy itself.<ref>[http://www.springerlink.com/content/j4276u12119nr290/ Paper by Wilson on the properties of such cones]</ref><ref>[http://www.springerlink.com/content/j4276u12119nr290/ Paper proposing a model for Ionization cone operation]</ref>

There is not yet a [[scientific consensus]] on the mechanics of such cones.

