{{Infobox organization | name = Society for Economic Botany | logo = SEB logo.gif | logo_size = 150px | motto = Fostering research and education on the past, present, and future uses of plants by people | formation = {{start date and age|1959}} | status = | purpose = Furthering [[economic botany]] | region = Worldwide | membership = | membership_year = | language = English | leader_title = President | leader_name = Steven Casper | main_organ = Council | website = {{URL|http://www.econbot.org/}} }} The '''Society for Economic Botany''' is an international [[learned society]] covering the field of [[economic botany]]. It was established in 1959. Its official [[Scientific journal|journal]] is [[Economic Botany (journal)|''Economic Botany'']], published on their behalf by [[Springer Science+Business Media]] and the [[New York Botanical Garden#Press|New York Botanical Garden Press]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.springer.com/life+sciences/plant+sciences/journal/12231 |title=Economic Botany |publisher=[[Springer Science+Business Media]] |accessdate=2016-11-26}}</ref> The society also publishes a biannual newsletter, ''Plants and People''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.econbot.org/index.php?module=content&type=user&func=view&pid=23 |title=Plants and People |publisher=Society for Economic Botany |accessdate=2016-11-26}}</ref> The president is [[Sunshine Brosi]] ([[Frostburg, MD]], United States).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.econbot.org/index.php?module=content&type=user&func=view&pid=8 |title=Society Officers |publisher=Society for Economic Botany |accessdate=2018-08-04}}</ref> The society organizes annual meetings at different locations around the world, where it awards the prize of Distinguished Economic Botanist to particularly meritorious individuals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bgci.org/news-and-events/news/0700/ |title=Two botanists recognised as Distinguished Economic Botanists by the Society of Economic Botany |publisher=[[Botanic Gardens Conservation International]] |accessdate=2016-11-26}}</ref><ref name=DEB />
